    Verse: 3
  Source:
    Title: Midrash Tanhama
Tags:
  - Grief
---
We rejoice over a birth and mourn over a death. But we should not. For
when a man is born, who knows what he will do or how he will end? But when
a man dies, we may rejoice -- if he left a good name and this world in peace.
